<h2><a name="error" id="error">#error</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>

Syntax:

</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#error message</span></pre>
<p>
The #error command simply causes the compiler to stop when it is encountered.
When an #error is encountered, the compiler spits out the line number and
whatever message is. This command is mostly used for debugging.
</p>

